2 tbsp, olive oil, divided
1, medium red onion, halved & cut into half-circles
1 tbsp, red wine vinegar
3/4 tsp, salt, divided
1/4 tsp, black pepper
1/2 tsp, anchovy paste
2 tbsp, chopped parsley
2 tbsp, chopped mint
2 tbsp, chopped basil
4, cod fillets (6 oz)
1/2 cup, dry white wine

1. Preheat oven to 400
2. Heat 1 tbsp OO in skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion and cook, stirring, about 5 minutes. Add vinegar and season w/ salt and pepper. Cook 30 seconds more. Spread onions into baking dish.
3. Heat 1 tbsp OO in same skillet on low. Add anchovy paste and cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Add parsley, mint, basil, 1/4 tsp salt, pinch of pepper.
4. Arrange fillets on top of onion and season with 1/2 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper. Spread herb paste over fillets.
5. Bake 15 minutes
